{
  "text": "Sections were prepared as previously described [CITATION_1] . Nissl staining was performed using Cresyl Violet solution (Muto Pure Chemicals). P8 cerebellar sections were used for detecting apoptosis via active caspase 3 immunostaining, followed by diaminobenzidine staining using a Vectastain ABC kit (Vector Laboratories) and Hematoxylin counterstaining. P5 sections obtained from Rac1 flox/flox ;Rac3 −/− ;tdTomato and Atoh1-Cre; Rac1 flox/flox ;Rac3 −/− ;tdTomato cerebellum were immunostained for Pax6, p27",
